<taxonomicName id="124199BF1291D441A55EE416836863AA" authority="Holdhaus, 1904" authorityName="Holdhaus" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Microlestes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microlestes luctuosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosus">Microlestes luctuosus (Holdhaus, 1904)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="435A05206FB313C84E5978D338AAE8EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D6397D61993DC2D27CB63C45074F81B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="946CD1B84320E783584E11317929382E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Southern Europe and Southwest Asia, widespread and common in Greece (
<bibRefCitation id="258DE45135C1D8D1A13D0CE13C106231" author="Arndt, E." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Ground Beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="987914C05DB4F2BC15F523AFF0634328" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0AA327992CF121E6354E4FC7C724B268" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D640BEB3C328A48A8558614DAA7F17AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
It prefers warm, dry places (
<bibRefCitation id="32140DF4C7CB0441EE80687EFDC2D5D8" author="Cardenas Talaveron, A." journalOrPublisher="Mediterranea Serie de Estudios Biologicos" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="147 - 163" title="Fenologia de las Espacies de Carabidos (ColeopteraCarabidae) Mas Abundantes en la Cuenca de Bembezar (NW. de la Provincia de Cordoba)" volume="8" year="1985">
<normalizedToken id="0E2A4E13602CD67282B46AD845AA1B9A" originalValue="Cárdenas">Cardenas</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="ED78FDF9CA05A6FCA275227A2E44DC06" originalValue="Talaverón">Talaveron</normalizedToken>
and Piella 1985
</bibRefCitation>
) on clayey soils (
<bibRefCitation id="A7188C012332570152F826418AE82F70" author="Trautner, J." journalOrPublisher="Josef Margraf, Aichtal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Tiger Beetles Ground Beetles. Illustrated Key to the Cicindelidae and Carabidae of Europe." year="1987">Trautner and Geigenmüller 1987</bibRefCitation>
). It may be found in areas of tall vegetation, those of over 20 cm in height (
<bibRefCitation id="78F483F383D1FC541F7A08352ABB79C6" author="Fadda, S." journalOrPublisher="Comptes Rendus Biologies" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="532 - 546" title="Consequences of the Cessation of 3000 Years of Grazing on Dry Mediterranean Grassland Ground-Active Beetle Assemblages." volume="331" year="2008">Fadda et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). In this study it was found in the cotton field in the heterogeneous area (n = 2), the cotton field in the homogeneous area (n = 1), the olive grove in the heterogeneous area (n = 57), the olive grove in the homogeneous area (n = 6), the wheat field in the heterogeneous area (n = 649) and the wheat field in the homogeneous area (n = 142).
</paragraph>
